<br>
I do not think it is an exploit, merely a clever manipulation of game mechanics.  However, that is an extremly thin line, and when 'manipulating game mechanics' becomes too easy, it should take some consideration.<br>
<br>
Manipulating the assist list with FD like that takes a much higher amount of timing and greater number of trials, that it does not trivialize this with 'fade splitting'.  The main issue, is that if you give someone infinite amount of time, anyone can split anything and get it single at the raid.  The reason why I drive my pullers insane and because only bards pull, is because I want the pull *NOW* and single.  I don't have time to wait for a monk to 'shuffle' a mob for 10 minutes until it becomes single.  Bellow does not make any pulls that are impossible/possible it just makes pulls that would normally force guild to wait 5 or so minute on the pullers become instaneous.<br>
<br>
Can other classes use the fact that assist call does not reset instantly?  Yes, however, try pulling that off with 'just' a monk FD'ing, and while it is possible it is incredibly difficult, with a bard it is easier by several degrees of magnitude.<br>
<br>
Seconds, Tounces playing the 'I figured it out on my own card' makes me laugh.  Yes, once someone explained it it made perfect sense.  Yes, when watching someone do it I immediately figured out what they were trying to do.  No, I do not believe you figured it out without seeing someone else do it first or someone else explaining what to do.<br>
